   For politicians, what counts is interest. They are ready to dine with their cruelest enemy; so far as their interests will be served. All what politicians live for is today; and they care less of yesterday and what tomorrow may bring. This side of politicians was recently shown in a former governor in one of the south-west states who dumped his party midway into a governorship election upon the promise and the allure of a ministerial seat. The politician, who has had cause to jump ship a couple of time, has received a huge backlash for his recent movement. While trying to play down the narratives of his movement, many didn’t see him as convincing. However, the gist in some quarters is that the former governor was actually looking for a ministerial seat and it was the allure that made him jump ship as at when he did. But will he succeed in his pursuit? Only time will tell. The quest for power ahead of the 2019 general elections has triggered a gale of defections as politicians across the various political divides are moving in their numbers to platforms on which they hope to actualise their respective ambitions, FELIX NWANERI reports   In advance democracies, reasons adduced by politicians… In “Politics” Lagos State Deputy Governor, Dr. Idiat Adebule, was recently caught in the loyalty web, when she was to make a choice between her principal, Governor Akinwunmi Ambode and Mr. Babajide Sanwo- Olu, who was the choice of the leadership of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state during the… In “Politics” With the 2019 elections around the corner, politicians with penchant for cross carpeting are in talks for the umpteenth time, to jump the ship. BIYI ADEGOROYE and PHILIP NYAM examine the list and the prospects The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) chairman in Adamawa State, Alhaji Abdulrahman Bobboi first flew the… In “Politics”